    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 20 November 1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>When his globe is ready, Giacomo Fagnano should hand it over to Jakob
                            Radich de Bannisis, who will get it to him quickly. Lodovico Gritti has
                            been lost, along with his brother and son. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Idem Nicolao Olao summe suo salutem. </p>
                <p>Globus meus si perfectus est, <persName>Iacobo Fagnano</persName><note
                        type="critic">Giacomo Fagnano.</note> negotiatori Mediolanensi, qui
                        <placeName>Antverpiae</placeName> agit, fac, per
                        <persName>Bannisium</persName><note type="critic">Jakob Radich de Bannisis
                        the Younger.</note> tradatur. Is enim a me in mandatis habet, ut quamprimum
                    eundem ad me mittat. <persName>Gritteus</persName><note type="critic">Lodovico
                        Gritti.</note> cum fratre et filio periit.<note type="critic">Gritti was
                        killed along with his two sons on 29 September, 1534, during the siege of
                        Mediaș.</note> Utinam regi nostro omnia feliciter et ex sententia succedant,
                    magnum certe adversarium fortuna ei intercepit. Vale et amicos omnes iubebis ex
                    me salvere. </p>
                <p><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> XX. Novembris 1534.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
